  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nLimestone\n\"Stone, with a hint of lime.\"\n×3\nTab\nTier\n10\nDropped by\n()\n\"limestone\"\n“Could be a useful building material.”\n–Wilson\n“It's made of crushed, dead fishies.”\n–Willow\n“Corals were crushed to make tiny rock.”\n–Wolfgang\n“When coral dies it hardens into stone.”\n–Wendy\n“CORAL DERIVATIVE”\n–WX-78\n“Commonly used in architecture.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I crushed up that pretty coral to make this.”\n–Woodie\n“Perhaps this sealife's death will find use after all.”\n–Maxwell\n“Sedimentary rock composed of coral.”\n–Wagstaff\n“Hard as an unripe fruit.”\n–Wigfrid\n“So bumpy!”\n–Webber\n“That's some tough stuff.”\n–Walani\n“Made from petit fishy skeletons.”\n–Warly\n“No good fer ship buildin'.”\n–Woodlegs\n“YON LIME AND STONE”\n–Wilba\n“Where pretty parts go?”\n–Wormwood\n“I sacrificed color in favor of usefulness.”\n–Wheeler\nLimestone is a Refined Item exclusive to the Shipwrecked DLC and crafted with 3 Corals. A Science Machine is required to unlock the recipe. Limestone can be used to craft a Chiminea, a Buoyant Chiminea, an Encrusted Boat, a Tar Extractor, a Sea Yard, a Sea Lab, a Limestone Suit, Coral Nubbins, Limestone Walls, Sea Walls or Ballphin Palaces. It can however not be used to repair Limestone Walls, as Rocks can be used to repair Stone Walls.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×6\n×6\n×4\n×4\n×3\n×6\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×6\n×6\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×2\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×4\n×6\n×4\n×4\n×2\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nLimestone is a type of sedimentary rock made of dead shells or coral and other sediments compacted together by heat and pressure over time to make solid rock.\nGallery[edit | edit source]\nLimestone on the ground.\nDSTDSRoGSWHam\nView or edit this template\nDon't Starve Together Craftable Items\nRegular Filters\nSurvivor Items\nWilson\nWillow\nWolfgang\nWendy\nWX-78\nWickerbottom\nWoodie\nWes\nMaxwell\nWigfrid\nWebber\nWarly\nWortox\nWormwood\nWinona\nWurt\nWalter\nWanda\nTools\nLight Sources\nPrototypers