  "wikitext": "{{Exclusivity|Shipwrecked}}\n{{Item Infobox\n|description = Stone, with a hint of lime.\n|tier = 1\n|tab = Refine\n|ingredient1 = Coral\n|multiplier1 = 3\n|stack = 10\n|spawnCode = \"limestone\"\n|droppedBy = {{pic32|Coral Reef}} ({{pic32|Hammer}})}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = Could be a useful building material.\n|willow = It's made of crushed, dead fishies.\n|wolfgang = Corals were crushed to make tiny rock.\n|wendy = When coral dies it hardens into stone.\n|wx78 = CORAL DERIVATIVE\n|wickerbottom = Commonly used in architecture.\n|woodie = I crushed up that pretty coral to make this.\n|maxwell = Perhaps this sealife's death will find use after all.\n|wagstaff = Sedimentary rock composed of coral.\n|wigfrid = Hard as an unripe fruit.\n|webber = So bumpy!\n|walani = That's some tough stuff.\n|warly = Made from petit fishy skeletons.\n|woodlegs = No good fer ship buildin'.\n|warbucks = A stone frequently seen in temples.\n|wilba = YON LIME AND STONE\n|wormwood = Where pretty parts go?\n|wheeler = I sacrificed color in favor of usefulness.\n|choose = woodie}}\n'''Limestone''' is a [[Refine]]d [[Item]] exclusive to the ''[[Don't Starve: Shipwrecked|Shipwrecked]]'' DLC and crafted with 3 [[Coral]]s. A [[Science Machine]] is required to unlock the recipe. Limestone can be used to craft a [[Chiminea]], a [[Buoyant Chiminea]], an [[Encrusted Boat]], a [[Tar Extractor]], a [[Sea Yard]], a [[Sea Lab]], a [[Limestone Suit]], [[Coral Nubbin]]s, [[Wall|Limestone Walls]], [[Wall|Sea Walls]] or [[Ballphin Palace]]s. It can however not be used to repair Limestone Walls, as [[Rocks]] can be used to repair [[Wall|Stone Walls]].\n\n=={{Pic32|Icon Tools}} Usage==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Sand\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Log\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Chiminea}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 6\n|item2 = Tar\n|count2 = 6\n|item3 = Sand\n|count3 = 4\n|result = Buoyant Chiminea}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Rope\n|count2 = 3\n|item3 = Boards\n|count3 = 6\n|result = Encrusted Boat\n|tool = Alchemy Engine}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Bamboo\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Coconut\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Tar Extractor}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 6\n|item2 = Tar\n|count2 = 6\n|item3 = Log\n|count3 = 4\n|result = Sea Yard}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Sand\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Electrical Doodad\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Sea Lab\n|tool = Science Machine}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Rope\n|count2 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Limestone Suit}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 3\n|item2 = Coral Larva\n|count2 = 1\n|result = Coral Nubbin\n|tool = Science Machine}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 2\n|tool = Alchemy Engine\n|result = Limestone Wall}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 2\n|item2 = Seaweed\n|count2 = 4\n|result = Sea Wall\n|tool = Science Machine\n|resultcount=6}}\n\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Limestone\n|count1 = 4\n|item2 = Seaweed\n|count2 = 4\n|item3 = Dorsal Fin\n|count3 = 2\n|result = Ballphin Palace\n|tool = Science Machine}}\n\n=={{Pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia==\n* Limestone is a type of sedimentary rock made of dead shells or coral and other sediments compacted together by heat and pressure over time to make solid rock.\n\n== {{Pic|32|Blueprint}} Gallery ==\n<gallery captionalign=\"center\" hideaddbutton=\"true\">\nLimestoneScreenshot.png|Limestone on the ground.\n</gallery>\n\n{{Craftable Items}}\n[[Category:Minerals]]\n[[Category:Non-Flammable]]\n[[Category:Refine Tab]]"
